The research results of students playing the leading role in the annual meeting of Zhejiang University make people's brains open - Xinhua English.news.cn
Washing hands with air, judging diseases with a breath, and accurately searching for the source of smog. Last night, at the opening ceremony of the 2016 academic annual meeting of Zhejiang University, a series of academic achievements with brain-opening holes were commended.
The main researchers of these achievements are students, and their research covers various fields such as environment, machinery, energy, medical care, life science, and humanities education. The students started from a curious idea and created many high-end inventions with application value , some of which have been awarded nationally and internationally.
Biosensors: Your Home Medical Examiner
The team of Zhang Diming, a doctoral student in the School of Biomedical Engineering, demonstrated a smartphone-side biosensor, which is only half the size of a smartphone.
"You only need to take a breath, and this instrument can initially detect the health of your body from the composition of the gas you exhale."
Zhang Diming said that the sensor is connected to the smartphone, and after exhaling the breath, the health report will be displayed on the phone.
Smart bracelets on the market that can detect health conditions generally detect physical parameters such as temperature and pulse.
This biosensor uses graphene, a new material, its target is chemical elements, and its keen "smell" allows it to reflect the health of the body more deeply and accurately.
Smart Surgical Lights: The Doctor's High-Energy Eye
In addition to smartphones, smart surgical lights are also used in operating rooms.
The invention won a silver medal at this year's 44th International Exhibition of Inventions in Geneva, Switzerland.
The team of master students Zhu Linjing and Shen Junfei from the School of Optoelectronic Science and Engineering opened up new ideas in the shortcomings of traditional surgical lights and invented the intelligent LED surgical shadowless light.
"A lot of diseases are detected early, and the excision is not in place, which is related to the lights used by doctors in the operating room."
Shen Junfei said, for example, in the early stage of cancer examination, if the doctor cannot see all the tumor tissue in time, the cancer cells will spread later.
This smart surgical light has four light discs that adjust the spectrum to enhance the differentiation of different tissues under illumination.
During the operation, the doctor can adjust the spot size, brightness, spectrum, color uniformity and shadowless rate at any time according to the needs of the operation and personal habits.
This smart surgical light has been tried out in hospitals such as Run Run Shaw Hospital Affiliated to Zhejiang University School of Medicine and Children's Hospital Affiliated to Zhejiang University School of Medicine, and has received good feedback.
Last October, the invention won the first prize of the National Challenge Cup.
Washing hands with air: water saving and cool
Ordinary people wash their hands with water, at most, wipe some soap and squeeze some hand sanitizer, while Li Qizhang and other students have invented a set of "air hand washing device".
Our body weight compresses the air just by standing on the sink of the device.
"It's like a pump.
The compressed air forms a fluid at the faucet and combines with the water.
That way, we can wash our hands clean! "
The color reaction and bacterial residue experiments prove that the effect of washing hands by this method is the same as that of ordinary hand washing.
This device only needs to rely on our own gravity as the drive, which can not only ensure the degree of cleaning, but also save 90% of water. The whole process is completely energy-free, energy-saving and environmentally friendly.
Last year, at the second Global Grand Challenge Summit, this invention stood out among many top universities in the world and won the only gold award.
Chongqing secondary vocational school pilots modern apprenticeship system enrollment is enterprise prospective employees - Xinhua English.news.cn
Yesterday, the reporter learned from the Municipal Education Commission that starting this year, our city will pilot the "modern apprenticeship" talent training model in 60 secondary vocational schools. Students who receive the pilot training will have apprenticeship status at the same time. unit employees.
According to the requirements of the Municipal Education Commission, the admission and employment procedures of secondary vocational schools and enterprises should be standardized, and the dual identities of apprentices of secondary vocational school students and prospective employees of enterprises should be clarified. According to the principle of two-way selection, apprentices, schools and enterprises should sign tripartite agreements. For apprentices under the age of 18, an agreement must be signed by the apprentice, guardian, school and enterprise to determine the rights and interests of all parties and the specific positions, teaching content, and rights and interests protection of the apprentices on-the-job training.
