South African doctor: Omicron has strong transmission but mostly mild symptoms
Many doctors and medical experts in South Africa believe that the Omicron variant of the new coronavirus causes milder symptoms than the delta variant, although it spreads faster.
According to the Associated Press, as the Omicron variant spreads in South Africa, a physician group of more than 5,000 doctors in Gauteng, South Africa, reported that the new crown patients they are currently treating have mild symptoms, such as physical Flu-like symptoms such as pain and cough.
Dr Unben Pillay, the group's director, said he sees dozens of patients every day, but none have yet to be hospitalized.
"They were able to control the disease at home and most recovered within 10 to 14 days of isolation," Pillay said.
That includes older patients and those with medical conditions, who would otherwise be more likely to become seriously ill from the coronavirus, he said.
In contrast, in the last wave of Delta, he said, the Covid-19 patients he treated had "difficulty breathing and low blood oxygen levels.
Many will be hospitalized within days."
In the two weeks after the first report of the mutant Omicron strain in southern Africa, other doctors shared similar experiences.
While it will take several weeks to gather enough data, observations from doctors and early evidence provide some clues.
According to the summary of the National Institute of Infectious Diseases in South Africa: Only 30% of new crown patients hospitalized in recent weeks have severe illness, which is half of the severe proportion of the previous wave; the average hospital stay has been shortened from 8 days to 2.8 days; the recent new crown disease Only 3% of patients died, compared with 20% of cases in the early outbreak in South Africa.
"At the moment, almost all indications are that this is a milder disease," said Willem Hanekom, director of the African Health Institute, citing data from the National Institute of Infectious Diseases and other reports.
He added: "It's still early days and we need to get late data.
Typically, hospitalizations and deaths come later, and we're only two weeks into this wave. "
Meanwhile, scientists around the world are watching case numbers and hospitalization rates, while testing the effectiveness of current vaccines and treatments.
While Delta remains the world's dominant strain of the new coronavirus, Omicron cases are emerging in dozens of countries, with South Africa at the center of the outbreak.
Gauteng saw a 400 per cent increase in new cases in the first week of December, according to health officials, with tests showing the Omicron variant accounted for more than 90 per cent of cases.
Education Review: What to Rely on to Save Abducted Children?
If we compare the famous PSA slogan "No business, no killing", then, in a good environment where there is no demand for "abduction", mass prevention and control and anti-trafficking will make abduction unprofitable, risky, and costly. high, such crimes will not happen again and again.
Recently, an emergency release platform for information on missing children developed by the Criminal Investigation Bureau of the Ministry of Public Security was launched.
This is an Internet information platform created to establish an authoritative channel for the release of information on missing children and to retrieve abducted children in a timely manner.
When I heard that this app is called "Reunion", I felt warm.
The new technology is not only named "literary and artistic" and full of feelings, but also the informatization is properly used, practical and effective.
The primary goal of anti-abduction law enforcement is to retrieve the abducted children and protect their personal safety and freedom.
The second is the trial and punishment of the suspect.
The meaning of criminal punishment, from individual punishment, social prevention to legal education, can be enumerated many "big words".
However, before the abduction and trafficking case is solved, priority should be given to the personal safety of the victim.
Prioritize matters, and under the urgent purpose of "seeking rescue", such as "whether child abduction should be the death penalty" and other controversial and controversial topics, they can be put on hold and discussed with caution; but the rescue of abducted children, etc. Must not.
According to the investigation experience of such cases, traffickers are accustomed to stay away from the crime site as soon as possible after they succeed.
If the kidnapping operation is delayed for one more minute, the child may be one step further away from the parent, and the difficulty of detecting the case will increase by one point.
In this case, it is indeed a pragmatic action to come up with an effective method such as the "Reunion" platform that directly helps to detect the case and retrieve the child.
After all, "fighting kidnapping" is a big task that requires the operation of the entire legal system.
Combating crime and protecting the rights and interests of children and parents, from the improvement of legislation, to the protection of the judiciary, and the meticulous law enforcement, all need to implement the care of "protecting the children and helping the weak".
In addition, the prevention of child trafficking, from the family to the society, can be done better.
For example, in a common case, a family of three rested at the train station, the parents were asleep, only to wake up to find that the child was missing.
A two-year-old child cannot be expected to have adequate self-protection skills, but as a parent of a young child, at least a fair amount of protection should be exercised.
Taking turns resting between parents, or keeping children under secure protection, is the least possible way to prevent child abduction.
From the other side of the police's crackdown on abduction and trafficking, the party who buys abducted children should also be concerned and punished.
A single wrongful act is often just one link in a long chain.
According to my country's "Criminal Law", the statutory penalty for child abduction and trafficking is 5 years; if the circumstances are particularly serious, it can be sentenced to death and confiscation of property.
Under the general trend of "light punishment", the crime of child abduction is obviously a crime with heavier punishment.
But there are still a lot of trafficking cases every year.
It can be seen that some people have a backward concept in raising children, and their legal awareness is weak.
Legal education for these people should be followed up simultaneously.
To effectively control the crime of trafficking, we cannot rely solely on the authorities to strictly enforce the law.
If the “market” for abductions and abductions exists widely, the traffickers are fascinated by their own interests, constantly innovate the means of abduction and trafficking, and form a situation of “fighting” with law enforcement officers, the anti-trafficking operation will inevitably fall into the quagmire of inefficiency.
Therefore, getting rid of outdated concepts and popularizing legal knowledge will also help to eradicate the crime of kidnapping and buying children.
