Saudi Arabia has reopened its border with Qatar.
Saudi Arabia and Egypt are spearheading efforts to restore relations with Qatar through the appointment of new ambassadors in Qatar.
Resolving differences in Gulf Arab states to restore relations with Qatar stems from a demand for solidarity for the interests of all countries and regional stability, aimed at addressing common challenges.
