The 725-kilometer-long corridor connecting the two countries will facilitate travel for citizens of the two countries and integrate supply chains.
Saudi Arabia's Public Investment Fund (PIF) will invest $5 billion in Oman, and companies from the two countries have signed 13 memorandums of understanding for cooperation worth $30 billion.
