Educational thinking: How to make "student tyrants" and "student scumbags" get their own way in college exams - Xinhua English.news.cn
Three students from Lanzhou Jiaotong University wrote to the school leaders to reflect their confusion about the university exam, and proposed to increase the difficulty of the exam and change the type of exam questions to make the exam truly reflect the students' actual level.
Indeed, college exams have long been a "hot topic".
On a university campus, students come from all over the world, with different levels of ability, combined with different levels of learning, and learning situations vary widely.
It is inevitable that there will be different feelings in the assessment of groups with such diverse characteristics.
Of course, if the exam questions are of a single type, the repetition rate is high, and the questions are too simple, it will inevitably lead to another completely different feeling.
Students who do not work hard may pass the exam by focusing on the attack before the test. If they think of other methods, they may achieve twice the result with half the effort.
As a result, there is a "strange situation" that "student scumbags" can pass the test without any investment, and even get high marks; .
From this point of view, the students of Lanzhou Jiaotong University reported that the problems in the university examinations are not without reason, and I believe this situation is not only in Lanzhou Jiaotong University.
In this sense, I would like to praise these three students who wrote directly.
In fact, anyone who has gone to college knows that it is not uncommon to prepare for the test unexpectedly, to "take" test questions from teachers in various ways, to try to delineate the scope of the test, and to obtain "key tutoring" before the test, even in the test. It is not uncommon to have cheat sheets and begged teachers to raise their hands after exams.
In the author's opinion, as a teaching quality evaluation guide, measuring the passing of a university examination depends more on teachers' comprehensive grasp of teaching and learning, as well as scientific propositions based on this.
Entering the undergraduate stage, majors begin to be subdivided, and many professional courses focus on basic knowledge.
Undoubtedly, whether or not to fully grasp the basic knowledge points of a subject is the content to be examined in the university examination.
Undergraduate knowledge is basically subject-based theories and basic common sense. From a knowledge point of view, there is not much room for change, and it is basically fixed.
As some teachers said, "The basic knowledge of college mathematics 20 years ago is still being learned, and it is still the key point."
However, the knowledge points are basically unchanged, which does not mean that the test questions are single and the test questions are repeated.
In many universities, test groups are generally formed into question groups, and then senior teachers of the subject co-ordinate the test papers to form the test papers. The examination papers are also participated by all the teachers responsible for the subject, so that the duplication of test questions can be overcome to a certain extent.
However, it is necessary to formulate a set of test questions that conform to the actual teaching and learning situation. The difficulty of the questions is normally distributed according to the overall situation of students' learning. It is also necessary to comprehensively grasp the teaching situation and comprehensively analyze the degree of students' learning, so as to make the test propositions difficult, easy, and difficult. The question type has a dynamic grasp, which can not only highlight the basic knowledge examination, but also take into account the ability examination, and at the same time carry out innovative design of the question type.
Exams are the baton of university education. What kind of exams there are, students will have corresponding preparation plans. If things go on like this, it will affect the effectiveness of university education.
Lanzhou Jiaotong University attaches great importance to the letter of recommendation from students, and has deployed a rectification plan throughout the school.
Each teaching unit is required to organize teachers to carry out seminars and self-examination of course end-of-course examinations, formulate test paper propositions and related systems, and at the same time strengthen the supervision and inspection of test paper propositions and review links, refine score evaluation, and strengthen curriculum teaching. Comprehensive examination.
Mechanistically solving problems such as single type of test questions and repeated questions is an issue that university examination affairs need to face. Of course, corresponding systems need to be introduced, but the effort is expensive in daily life, and teachers need to have a comprehensive grasp of the teaching situation, not only to understand the teaching content thoroughly, It is even more necessary to thoroughly understand the students' learning situation, and to understand both sides, teaching and learning will be better connected, forming a positive interaction, and examinations will be more realistic, so that "students" and "students" have their own place.
