Xinhua News Agency, Tianjin, December 12 (Reporter Zhou Runjian) Astronomy science experts introduced that as the last large-scale meteor shower of the year, the Geminid meteor shower, one of the three major meteor showers in the northern hemisphere, will usher in a great event on December 14. Friends who like meteor showers Observations can be made in the second half of the day.
The Geminid meteor shower taken by Beijing astronomy enthusiast Anjiu in Qinghai on December 13, 2018.
The parent body of most meteor showers is a periodic comet, but the parent body of the Geminid meteor shower is the asteroid 3200 Faeton, an Apollo-type asteroid.
The Geminid meteor shower is also the second known meteor shower that is not "bred" by a comet.
Xiu Lipeng, director of the Tianjin Astronomical Society and an expert in astronomy popularization, said that just like the New Year's blockbuster, the Geminid meteor shower generally appears at the end of the year, and the "release schedule" can last from December 4th to 17th.
The meteor shower is known for its large flow and stability. Together with the Quadrantid meteor shower and the Perseid meteor shower, it is known as the three major meteor showers in the northern hemisphere.
A notable feature of the Geminid meteor shower is the slow speed of meteoroids, rich colors, and a lot of fireballs, which are suitable for both visual and astrophotography beginners.
The Geminid meteor shower taken by Tianjin astronomy enthusiast Yang Jing in Jizhou, Tianjin on December 13, 2020.
Astronomical forecasts show that this year's Geminid meteor shower will usher in a maximum at around 15:00 on December 14, with a maximum time of ZHR (under ideal observation conditions, when the radiant is directly overhead, the number of meteors that can be seen per hour) is 150.
Geminid meteor shower recommended index chart.
"Last year, the 'Beautiful' Geminid meteor shower left a deep impression on people, but this year's Geminid meteor shower will be disturbed by moonlight, which will be a little less exciting.
The 14th is the eleventh day of the eleventh month of the lunar calendar. The moon phase is a gibbous moon. The bright moonlight will interfere with the observation. Fortunately, the moon will fall in the second half of the night, and the radiant point of the Geminid meteor shower will also rise relatively high.
Friends who like meteor showers can observe in the second half of the night when the moon is behind, but pay attention to keeping warm and cold. "
How can we observe as many meteors as possible?
"It is not recommended to observe in the city. You can choose a place with a high altitude, low light pollution, and a wide field of vision facing the northeast in the suburbs or villages, and then wait patiently until the moon sets, and then you can observe it visually.
It should be noted that the flow of the Geminid meteor shower is very large in all directions, so there is no need to stare at the radiant of the Geminid meteor shower all the time.
If you like photography, if you want to shoot a gorgeous 'meteor shower blockbuster', it is best to choose a wide-angle, large-aperture lens, and use a high ISO and maximum aperture when shooting.
For stability and continuity, a tripod, spare batteries and a cable release are also essential. "
Xiu Lipeng reminded.
